This program allows user to edit an image file in various ways, including flipping,
creating a greyscale image, brightening, blurring, and sharpening an image.

Here are the commands the user could use:

<1> Load an image.
Use this command to load an image. This command should be used before any operations below in order
to have the content of the image saved in the program.
Command: blur <destination image name> <source image name>
Example: blur testImages/image.png image

<2> Flip an image.
Use this command to flip an image horizontally or vertically.
Command: flip-<direction> <destination image name> <source image name>
Example: flip-vertical testImages/image.png image

<3> Brighten/Darken an image.
Use this command to make an image brighter or darker by a specified amount.
Command: brighten <level of brightness/darkness> <destination image name> <source image name>
Note: Use a negative number if you want to darken the image instead of brightening it.
Example: brighten 10 testImages/image.png image

<4> Create a greyscale image of an image.
Use this command to create a greyscale image with the specified component.
Command: greyscale-<the component to greyscale> <destination image name> <source image name>
Note: This program allows user to create an greyscale image with 7 different components - red,
green, blue, intensity, luma, value, and sepia.
Example: greyscale-red testImages/image.png image

<5> Blur an image.
Use this command to blur an image.
Command: blur <destination image name> <source image name>
Example: blur testImages/image.png image

<6> Sharpen an image.
Use this command to sharpen an image.
Command: sharpen <destination image name> <source image name>
Example: sharpen testImages/image.png image

<7> Color Transformation.
Use this command to transform the color tone of the image, luma to create greyscale and sepia to
create a reddish brown tone.
Command (Greyscale): color-luma <destination image name> <source image name>
Note: This command creates the same result as using the command:
greyscale-luma <destination image name> <source image name>
Example: color-luma testImages/image.png image
Command (Sepia): color-sepia <destination image name> <source image name>
Example: color-sepia testImages/image.png image

<8> Save an image.
Use this command to save an image at the specified location.
Command: save <destination image name> <source image name>
Example: save testImages/image.png image
